      <div id="mainContent" class="main column clearfix"> 
       <h1>Greek Military History</h1> 
       <p><strong>General</strong></p> 
       <ul class="checklist"> 
        <li>Adcock, F.E. <em>The Greek and Macedonian Art of War</em>, Berkeley, 1957.</li> 
        <li>Anderson, J.K. <em>Military Theory and Practice in the Age of Xenophon</em>, Berkeley, 1970.</li> 
        <li>Best, J.G.P. <em>Thracian Peltasts and Their Influence on Greek Warfare</em>, Groeningen, 1969.</li> 
        <li>Bettalli, M. "Enea Tattico e l'insegnamento dell'arte militare," <em>AFLS</em> 7 (1986) 73-89.</li> 
        <li>Chase, G.H., <em>Shield Devices of the Greeks in Art and Literature</em></li> 
        <li>Connor, W.R., "Early Greek Land Warfare as Symbolic Expression," <em>Past and Present</em> 119 (1988), pp. 3-28.</li> 
        <li>Delbrueck, Hans, <em>History of the Art of War</em>, Vol. 1, Warfare in Antiquity (Trans. 1975).</li> 
        <li>DeSouza, Philip, <em>Piracy and the Graeco-Roman World</em>, Cambridge, 1999.</li> 
        <li>Ferrill, Arther, The Origins of War: From the Stone Age to Alexander the Great, reviewed by A.M. Devine in <em>CW</em> 81 (1987-88).</li> 
        <li>Gabriel, R.A. and Metz, K., <em>From Sumer to Rome: The Military Capabilities of Ancient Armies</em>, 1991.</li> 
        <li>Garlan, Yvon, <em>Recherches de Poliorcetique Grecque</em>, Paris: Boccard, 1974.</li> 
        <li>Greenhalgh, P.A.L. <em>Early Greek Warfare</em>, Cambridge, 1973.</li> 
        <li>Griffith, G.T. <em>The Mercenaries of the Hellenistic World</em> Groningen, 1968.</li> 
        <li>Hackett, J., <em>Warfare in the Ancient World</em>, 1989.</li> 
        <li>Hanson, Victor Davis, <em>The Western Way of War: Infantry Battle in Classical Greece</em>, 1989.</li> 
        <li>Hanson, Victor Davis, <em>The Wars of the Greeks</em>, London: Cassell, 1999.</li> 
        <li>Havelock, Eric, "War as a way of life in Classical Culture," in <em>Classical Values and the Modern World</em>. Vannier Lectures, Ottawa 1972 19-78.</li> 
        <li>Hunt, P. Slaves, <em>Warfare and Ideology in the Greek Historians</em></li> 
        <li>Kern, P.B., <em>Ancient Siege Warfare</em>, Bloomington: Indiana University Press, 1999.</li> 
        <li>Kromayer, J. and Veith, G., Heerwesen und Kriegfuhrung der Griechen und Romer, 1928.</li> 
        <li>Lawrence, Arnold Walter, <em>Greek Aims in Fortification</em>, Oxford, 1980</li> 
        <li>Lazenby, J. F. <em>The Spartan Army</em>, Warminster England: Aris &amp; Phillips, 1985.</li> 
        <li>Marsden, E.W. <em>Greek and Roman Artillery. Historical Development and Technical Treatises</em>, 2 vols. Oxford</li> 
        <li>Plasart, A., "Les archers d'Athenes," <em>REG</em> 26 (1913) pp. 151-213.</li> 
        <li>Pritchett, W.K. <em>The Greek State at War</em>, Berkeley &amp; Los Angeles, 1971-1991, Vols. 1-5</li> 
        <li>Sage, Michael, <em>Warfare in Ancient Greece. A Sourcebook</em>, London, 1996.</li> 
        <li>Sekunda, Nick "Greek Siege Warfare" Popular <em>Archaeology</em> Vol. 1, nr. 9 (March 1980) 10-14.</li> 
        <li>---------- &amp; McBride, Angus, <em>The Ancient Greeks, Armies of Classical Greece 5th &amp; 4th Centuries B.C.</em> (London, 1986), Osprey Publishing.</li> 
        <li>----------, "Warriors of Ancient Greece" <em>Archaeology Today</em> Vol. 8, nr. 1 (Feb. 1987) p. 6-10.</li> 
        <li>----------, "The Organization of the Lakedaimonian Army" monograph in preparation</li> 
        <li>----------. The Army of Alexander the Great London: Osprey 1984. Reviewed by Fisher <em>G&amp;R</em> 32 (1985) 90.</li> 
        <li>----------."Regimental Uniforms: A look at the Army of Alexander the Great" <em>Popular Archaeology</em> Vol. 5, No. 12, June 1984 15-16.</li> 
        <li>Snodgrass, A.M. <em>Arms and Armour of the Greeks</em>, London, 1967.</li> 
        <li>Snodgrass, A.M. <em>Early Greek Armour and Weapons</em>, Edinburgh, 1964.</li> 
